# 🧠 1. The **Exact Prompt** to Start Interactive Design Mode

Paste this into Claude Code:

```
Enter Interactive Architecture Design Mode.

Use the Design Mode Skill.

Your job is to guide me through designing the migration of our on‑prem Kubernetes, Postgres, RabbitMQ, and Prometheus stack to AWS.

Follow these rules:
- Ask clarifying questions before proposing any architecture.
- Explore multiple options with pros/cons.
- Use diagrams (Mermaid) when helpful.
- Break the design into phases (Landing Zone, EKS, RDS Postgres, Amazon MQ, AMP, networking, IAM).
- Do NOT generate Terraform or automation code until I explicitly say “Switch to automation mode”.
- Keep the conversation iterative and interactive.
- After each answer, ask me what I want to refine next.
```

This prompt **forces Claude into a loop** where it keeps asking questions and refining the design with you.

