# 🎮 3. Slash Command Version (Optional)

If you created `/design` in `.claude/commands/design.json`, then you simply type:

```
/design
```

Claude will automatically:

- Ask clarifying questions  
- Explore architecture options  
- Draw diagrams  
- Avoid Terraform until you switch modes  

---

# 🔁 4. The “Design Loop” Claude Will Follow

When you use the prompt above, Claude enters this loop:

### Step 1 — Ask clarifying questions  
(e.g., cluster size, RPO/RTO, HA requirements, network constraints)

### Step 2 — Propose architecture options  
(e.g., EKS vs ECS, RDS vs Aurora, Amazon MQ vs self‑managed)

### Step 3 — Provide diagrams  
(Mermaid diagrams for VPC, EKS, RDS, MQ, AMP)

### Step 4 — Provide trade‑offs  
(cost, complexity, operational load, migration risk)

### Step 5 — Ask what to refine  
(“Do you want to refine networking, data migration, or observability next?”)

### Step 6 — Repeat  
Until you say:

```
Switch to automation mode
```

Then it will generate Terraform.

